Reasoning: The paper discusses technical options for achieving high spectral efficiency in interference-limited cellular networks, which is a topic related to networked systems and communication. The paper specifically focuses on evaluating the achievable cell-edge performance on the uplink of multicell systems, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of soft-combining-based probabilistic data association (SC-PDA) receiver, which is related to information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the benefits of properly selecting the MRs' positions, which is related to computer systems and networking (cs.COMM) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the cell-edge MSs roaming near the angular direction halfway between two adjacent remote antennas, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) as it involves optimizing the performance of mobile devices in a multimedia-rich environment.
